# RDF 3.0.4 Release Notes

## Pipeline Asset Fix
Restructure Build stage in pipeline.svg as a numbered list matching the other
three stages; fix subtitle text that overflowed the box boundary.

## Starter Profile Promotion & Evidence Verification

Promotes Perl, PHP, and Infrastructure from starter to full-tier profiles
by adding 3 reference docs each (anti-patterns, testing, domain-specific).
Introduces two new evidence conventions: Verification Preamble (context-gate
for anti-pattern findings) and "When this is safe" inline annotations to
reduce false positives. Adds Evidence Discipline section to all testing
reference docs. Updates all 7 operational modes with evidence verification
discipline.

Key changes:
- 9 new reference docs across Perl, PHP, Infrastructure profiles
- Anti-patterns docs include Verification Preamble: scan→verify two-pass
- Inline "When this is safe" annotations prevent false positives
- Testing docs include Evidence Discipline: tests as evidence, not ceremony
- All modes (security, performance, migration, debugging, refactoring,
  documentation, development) gain evidence-backed verification requirements
- Registry updated: 0 starter profiles remain, all 11 profiles are full tier

---

## Parallel Plan Execution

Adds inter-phase parallel dispatch to `/r-build`. The build command
reads a structured dependency graph from PLAN.md, computes parallel
batches, validates file ownership, and dispatches multiple dispatcher
subagents concurrently with scope-derived isolation.

Key changes:
- `/r-build --parallel` auto-batches all pending phases by dependency graph
- `/r-build N-M` dispatches a specific range of phases in parallel
- Isolation auto-derived from scope: file-gated for multi-file, git
  worktree for cross-cutting/sensitive phases. `--worktree` flag overrides.
- Parallel failure handling with gate-aware recommendations
- Structured dependency list format (`- Phase N: none` / `- Phase N: [deps]`)
  replaces free-text ASCII dependency graphs
- VPE Stage 4 calls `/r-build --parallel` once (replaces per-phase loop)
- Dispatcher PARALLEL_BATCH flag prevents nested parallelism

---

## Documentation Convention

Adds a cross-project documentation convention to RDF as a brand-agnostic
product feature. The convention defines README structure, SVG asset
specifications, badge standards, companion file templates, and a
progressive documentation level system (floor/level-2/level-3).

Key changes:
- `reference/documentation-standard.md` (~350 lines): README template with
  section ordering rules, above-the-fold SVG specs, badge conventions,
  middle section numbering, companion file requirements, man page
  cross-referencing, and enforcement check inventory
- `reference/templates/SECURITY.md`: companion file template with
  `{{PROJECT}}` and `{{CONTACT_EMAIL}}` placeholders
- `reference/templates/CONTRIBUTING.md`: companion file template with
  `{{PROJECT}}`, `{{ORG}}`, and `{{LICENSE}}` placeholders
- Workspace `reference/brand.md`: rfxn brand definition (palette,
  typography, project identities) — not committed to RDF

---

## Init: Companion File Generation

Extends `rdf init` to generate SECURITY.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, and
`.rdf/docs-level` from templates. Companion files use `sed` substitution
with `|` delimiter for `{{PLACEHOLDER}}` variables.

Key changes:
- `_generate_companion_files()` creates SECURITY.md and CONTRIBUTING.md
  from `reference/templates/` if they don't already exist
- `.rdf/docs-level` created during init with profile-aware inference
  (products default to `level-2`, libraries to `floor`)
- Org resolved from `git remote get-url origin` with `rfxn` fallback
- Dry-run support, idempotent (skips existing files)

---

## Doctor: Readme Scope

Adds `rdf doctor --scope readme` for documentation convention enforcement.
The new `_check_readme()` function validates README.md structure against
project documentation level (floor, level-2, or level-3), read from
`.rdf/docs-level`.

Key changes:
- Floor checks (always run): README.md presence, badge row (shields.io or
  GitHub Actions), Quick Start section, License section, numbered sections
  (## N. format), ## 3. and ## 4. sections, exit codes table
- Level-2 checks: What's New, Contents (ToC), Integration section,
  SECURITY.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, banner SVGs (dark/light), picture tag
- Level-3 checks: Troubleshooting section, pipeline/architecture SVG,
  terminal demo asset
- `readme` scope added to `_doctor_one()` dispatch and usage text
- No README → early FAIL and return (no cascade)
- Unknown docs-level value defaults to floor

---

# RDF 3.0.3 Release Notes

## Gate Simplification & VPE Pipeline Orchestrator

Replaces the risk×type gate selection matrix with a 5-level scope
classification derived automatically by the dispatcher from phase content.
Restores v2-style per-agent finding qualifiers for self-routing.
Adds /r-vpe as an optional end-to-end pipeline orchestrator.

Key changes:
- Scope classification: dispatcher auto-derives scope (docs, focused,
  multi-file, cross-cutting, sensitive) from file list and governance
  context — replaces planner-tagged risk/type/gates matrix
- Finding qualifiers: shared severity spine (MUST-FIX/SHOULD-FIX/
  INFORMATIONAL) plus agent-scoped qualifiers that carry routing signals
  (merge-block, fix-or-refute, workflow-breaking, blocking-concern, etc.)
- Plan metadata simplified: 7 mandatory fields → 4 (Mode, Accept, Test,
  Edge cases) — Risk, Type, Gates removed from planner surface
- /r-vpe: optional pipeline orchestrator managing spec→plan→build→ship
  with adaptive intake (1-4 exchanges), approval gates between stages,
  and crash recovery via vpe-progress.md

Developer surface: 4 concepts (PASS, MUST-FIX, SHOULD-FIX, phase status
file). Scope classification is visible in framework.md for transparency
but requires no developer action.

---

# RDF 3.0.2 Release Notes

## Sentinel Integration & Quality Gate Redesign

Dispatcher-owned quality gate resolution restores the RDF 2.x mgr model.
Sentinel is now active on all non-trivial phases with automatic depth
scaling. The developer surface simplifies to ~6 concepts.

Key changes:
- Tiered sentinel depth: lite (2-pass: anti-slop + regression) for
  routine phases, full (4-pass) for scope:cross-cutting, scope:sensitive,
  end-of-plan, /r-ship, and /r-audit
- Counter-hypothesis protocol (unconditional in sentinel mode) prevents
  false positives — every MUST-FIX/CONCERN finding is evaluated against
  location-specific counter-evidence before reporting
- Parallel QA+sentinel execution: both agents run simultaneously, findings
  deduplicated by file:line proximity
- End-of-plan sentinel: mandatory full 4-pass review of cumulative diff
  after the last phase of any 3+ phase plan
- Dispatcher-owned finding resolution: fix/refute cycle (max 3 iterations)
  before escalating to the developer
- FP calibration: dispatcher re-dispatches sentinel at full depth when
  zero findings are reported on a 50+ line diff
- SHOULD-FIX renamed to CONCERN across all surfaces (later reverted to SHOULD-FIX in 3.0.3)

---

# RDF 3.0.1 Release Notes

## .rdf/ Directory Migration

All per-project RDF state consolidates into a single `.rdf/` directory:
- `.rdf/governance/` — governance files (was `.claude/governance/`)
- `.rdf/work-output/` — session state (was `work-output/`)
- `.rdf/memory/` — agent memory (was CC auto-memory path)
- `.rdf/scopes/` — sub-scope governance overrides

New `rdf migrate` command handles transition from old layout.
`rdf doctor` detects legacy state and recommends migration.

## Profile & Mode Expansion

Five new profiles (Rust, TypeScript, Perl, PHP, Infrastructure) and three
new modes (refactoring, debugging, documentation). Profiles are now
stackable — `rdf init` auto-detects multiple profiles and merges their
governance templates. Two tiers: full (template + reference docs) and
starter (template only).

Core governance template expanded with AI Agent Discipline, Code
Generation Standards, Context Window Hygiene, and Collaboration Protocol
sections that apply to every project.

---

# RDF 3.0.0 Release Notes

## What's New

RDF 3.0.0 is a complete architecture redesign. The prior domain-specific
agent model (12 agents with baked-in domain knowledge) is replaced by a
universal agent model (6 agents whose behavior is shaped by governance
files initialized per-project).

### Universal Agents
- **planner** (opus) -- research, specs, implementation plans
- **dispatcher** (sonnet) -- plan execution orchestrator
- **engineer** (opus) -- universal implementation, governance-driven
- **qa** (sonnet) -- verification gate
- **uat** (sonnet) -- user acceptance testing
- **reviewer** (opus) -- adversarial review (challenge + sentinel modes)

### /r- Command Namespace
24 commands replace the prior ~68:
- 14 lifecycle commands: /r-init, /r-start, /r-spec, /r-plan, /r-mode,
  /r-status, /r-refresh, /r-sync, /r-audit, /r-ship, /build, /verify,
  /test, /review
- 10 utility commands under /r-util- namespace

### Governance-Driven Profiles
Profiles no longer bundle agents and commands. All 6 agents and 24 commands
are always available. Profiles provide governance seed templates that
/r-init uses to initialize per-project governance files. The governance
files shape agent behavior at runtime.

## Migration from 2.x

### Automatic
Run `rdf generate claude-code` to regenerate. Symlinks remain unchanged.

### What Changed
- Agent names: `rfxn-` prefix replaced by `rdf-` (e.g., `rdf-engineer`)
- Commands: old slash commands replaced by `/r-` namespace equivalents
- Profiles: `profile.json` manifests removed (governance-template.md only)
- Dispatch: `lib/dispatch-agents.json` and `lib/dispatch-tasks.json` removed

### Preserved Artifacts
- `canonical/agents-v2-archived/` -- all 12 v2 agent definitions
- `canonical/commands-v2-archived/` -- all 68 v2 command definitions
- `adapters/claude-code/agent-meta-v2.json` -- v2 agent metadata

### Breaking Changes
- v2 slash commands (`/mgr`, `/sys-eng`, `/audit`, etc.) no longer exist
- `profile.json` files removed from all profiles
- `rdf_profile_includes` no longer gates agent/command generation
- `dispatch-agents.json` and `dispatch-tasks.json` removed
